<ITEM>CLV. Nor even the Elements of plain Geometry.</ITEM>
<ITEM>CLVI. The proper Objects of Sight incapable of be|ing managed as Geometrical Figures.</ITEM>
<ITEM>CLVII. The Opinion of tho&s;e who hold plain Figures to be the Immediate Objects of Sight, con&s;idered.</ITEM>
<ITEM>CLVIII. Plains no more the immediate Objects of Sight, than Solids.</ITEM>
<ITEM>CLIX. Difficult to enter preci&s;ely into the Thoughts of the above mentioned Intelligence.</ITEM>
<ITEM>CLX. The Object of Geometry, its not being &s;uffici|ently under&s;tood, cau&s;e of Difficulty and u&s;ele&s;s Labour in that Science.</ITEM>
</LIST>
